The paper deals with the problem of communication of random sources over networks to within a distortion criterion, which is a classic problem in information theory. The paper also discusses the use of common randomness and separation architectures, which are common techniques in information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with networks and communication between various users, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also mentions the possibility of computing network capacity, which suggests that it could belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
